==Chinese==

===Etymology===
From Chinese [[吉林]] (simplified and traditional); pinyin: Jílín; Wade-Giles: Chi-lin; the word probably originates from ''jilin wula'' (T: 吉林烏拉 / S: 吉林乌拉), the Chinese transcription of a Manchu term meaning "along the river"; the literal meaning of the Chinese characters for "Jilin" is "auspicious forest".

===Proper noun===
'''Jilin'''

# A province in northeastern China.

